title: Treviso Caesar Salad
summary: Treviso Caesar Salad might be a good recipe to expand your main course repertoire. One portion of this dish contains roughly 17g of protein, 17g of fat, and a total of 537 calories. This recipe serves 4 and costs $5.41 per serving. 1 person were glad they tried this recipe. It is an expensive recipe for fans of American food. If you have kosher salt and pepper, sourdough rolls, olive oil, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. To use up the kosher salt you could follow this main course with the Low Fat Crumbs Cake (Kosher-Dairy) as a dessert. It is brought to you by wholeliving.com. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes about 16 minutes. With a spoonacular score of 76%, this dish is pretty good.
